{
  "root_cause": "With SGLANG_USE_CUDA_IPC_TRANSPORT=1 but SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE=0 (the default), the sender's MmItemMemoryPool wraps each multimodal tensor in a CudaIpcTensorTransportProxy built via get_proxy_state(), which calls data.untyped_storage()._share_cuda_() on the pool-slice view and stores that per-tensor IPC handle in proxy_state['ipc_extra']['handle']. The receiver therefore takes the non-pooled branch in reconstruct_on_target_device (cuda_ipc_transport_utils.py:482) and opens a fresh torch.UntypedStorage._new_shared_cuda(*handle) for every reconstruct. Under concurrency-128 the underlying pool storage can be recycled/reused by the sender before the receiver gets to import that per-tensor handle, so the device pointer embedded in the handle refers to freed/recycled memory and HIP returns hipErrorInvalidDevicePointer; with the cache off there is no retry logic and the scheduler dies. Enabling SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE=1 switches _wrap_tensor_for_cuda_ipc to pass pool_ipc_handle=pool._pool_ipc_handle with a byte offset, so the receiver caches one _new_shared_cuda mapping of the pool storage and reuses it across reuses (and invalidates+reopens on failure).",
  "fix": "Set SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE=1 in /app/launch_qwen3.5_27b_sglang.sh (keeps SGLANG_USE_CUDA_IPC_TRANSPORT=1).",
  "evidence": "[2026-07-16 12:50:59 TP1] Failed to deserialize from CUDA IPC handle (HIP error: invalid device pointer ... reconstruct_on_target_device (cuda_ipc_transport_utils.py:488)) and [2026-07-16 12:50:59] SIGQUIT received ... It usually means one child failed. Line 488 is the non-pooled branch (open per-tensor handle directly with no cache/retry), so SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE must be turned on."
}

